TITLE: Custom Form Validation in MauticJS
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to implement custom form validation using the onValidate callback in MauticFormCallback. It allows overriding the default form validation and controlling form submission based on custom logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mautic/developer-documentation-new/blob/5.x/docs/components/tracking_script.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
MauticFormCallback['replaceWithFormName'] = {
    onValidate: function () {
        // before form validation
        var formIsGood = True;
        var dontUpdate = False;
        if(dontUpdate){
            return null;
        }else if(formIsGood){
            return True;
        }else if(!formIsGood){
            return False;
        }
    },
};
```

